$ General Mapping Tools 

{ Programs

  `→ tools/GMT/programs/grdraster`: Extract subsets (subregion) from a binary raster and save as GMT grid.

  `pscoast`: Create coastline maps. It uses → Wissenschaft/Geologie/Karten#gshhg[GSHHG] data.


}

{ Tutorial

  The tutorial files are located in → Linux/fhs/usr/share/doc/gmt/tutorial.

}

{ Variables

  → Linux/fhs/usr/share/gmt/conf/gmt_conf

}

{ Referencing GMT

  "
    Figures were drawn using the Generic Mapping Tools (Wessel and Smith, 1998)
  "

  "
    Wessel, P. and W.H.F. Smith (1998), New, improved version of the Generic Mapping Tools
    released, ~Eos Trans. AGU~, ~79~, 579.
  "

}

